Here are some steps you can take to use SDR to find the location of a drone:

1. Set up your SDR receiver. An SDR receiver is a device that receives and processes radio signals. You can purchase an SDR receiver or build one yourself using a software-defined radio (SDR) kit.
2. Connect the SDR receiver to your computer. Most SDR receivers have a USB or Ethernet port that can be connected to your computer. Once connected, the SDR software will allow you to tune into different frequencies and record the signals being transmitted by the drone.
3. Tune into the frequency of the drone's communication signals. You can use an online frequency database to determine which frequencies are being used by drones in your area. Once you have identified the frequency, you can tune into it using your SDR receiver and listen for any communication signals from the drone.
4. Record the communication signals from the drone. Once you have tuned into the correct frequency, you can begin recording the communication signals being transmitted by the drone. These signals will contain information about the drone's location, such as GPS coordinates and altitude.
5. Analyze the recorded data. After recording the communication signals from the drone, you can use software such as a spectrum analyzer to analyze them and determine their location and altitude. By analyzing these signals, you can determine where the drone is located and track its movements over time.
